associated_reports.name: Search IPA Subject
associated_reports.description:
Search subjects by name, phone, email or ID.
Leave the search field empty to see all subjects.
associated_reports.sql:
select distinct m.id master_id, 
pi.first_name, pi.middle_name, pi.last_name, pi.nick_name,
a.street, a.street2, a.city, a.state, a.zip, 
pc.data, pc.rec_type
from masters m
inner join player_infos pi
on pi.master_id = m.id 
inner join ipa_assignments b
on m.id = b.master_id
left join addresses a
on m.id = a.master_id
left join player_contacts pc
on pc.master_id = m.id
where 
(:name is null 
or pi.first_name ~* :name
or pi.last_name ~* :name
or pi.middle_name ~* :name
or pi.nick_name ~* :name
or( 
    pi.first_name ~* coalesce(split_part(:name, ' ', 1),'none')
    AND pi.last_name ~* coalesce(split_part(:name, ' ', 2),'none')
  )
) OR
(
length(:name) > 5 AND
regexp_replace(pc.data, '\W+', '', 'g') ~* regexp_replace(:name, '\W+', '', 'g')
) OR
(
b.ipa_id::varchar = :name
)
associated_reports.search_attrs:
name: 
  text: 
    all: true
    multiple: single

associated_reports.name: File Report
associated_reports.description: Enter one or more IPA IDs to view associated files (only those you have access to). Select one or more files with the checkboxes in the final column and click the Download button to download a zip file containing all the selected files.
associated_reports.sql:
select 
al.master_id,
ipa.ipa_id,
al.extra_log_type "session type",
al.select_status,
filestore_report_file_path(nfs_store_stored_files::nfs_store_stored_files, nfs_store_archived_files::nfs_store_archived_files) "file path", 
filestore_report_perform_action(c.id, 'activity_log__ipa_assignment_session_filestore', al.id, nfs_store_stored_files::nfs_store_stored_files, nfs_store_archived_files::nfs_store_archived_files) "perform action: download file",
filestore_report_select_fields(c.id, 'activity_log__ipa_assignment_session_filestore', al.id, nfs_store_stored_files.id, nfs_store_archived_files.id) "select items: download files"

from activity_log_ipa_assignment_session_filestores al

inner join ipa_assignments ipa
on al.master_id = ipa.master_id

inner join model_references mr
on mr.from_record_type = 'ActivityLog::IpaAssignmentSessionFilestore'
and al.master_id = mr.from_record_master_id
and al.id = mr.from_record_id

inner join nfs_store_containers c
on mr.to_record_type = 'NfsStore::Manage::Container'
and c.master_id = mr.to_record_master_id
and c.id = mr.to_record_id

inner join nfs_store_stored_files
on c.id = nfs_store_stored_files.nfs_store_container_id

left join nfs_store_archived_files
on nfs_store_stored_files.id = nfs_store_archived_files.nfs_store_stored_file_id

where ipa.ipa_id in (:ipa_ids) AND al.select_status IN ('open', 'closed')


AND :file_filtering_conditions_for_activity_log__ipa_assignment_session_filestore


order by 
  ipa_id, "session type", "file path", "perform action: download file"  
;
associated_reports.search_attrs:
ipa_ids: 
  number: 
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    label: IPA IDs
    disabled: false

associated_reports.name: IPA Find Container
associated_reports.description: Get a single Container ID for a subject. Used by IPA script-based uploads.
associated_reports.sql:
select 

  mr.to_record_id "container_id",
  al.id "activity_log_id",
  'activity_log__ipa_assignment_session_filestore' "activity_log_type"
--  , 
--  al.extra_log_type "session_type", 
--  al.session_date, 
--  al.session_time, 
--  al.select_status, 
--  ipa.ipa_id 
from activity_log_ipa_assignment_session_filestores al
inner join ipa_assignments ipa 
  on 
    al.master_id = ipa.master_id
inner join model_references mr
  on 
    from_record_type = 'ActivityLog::IpaAssignmentSessionFilestore'
    and from_record_id = al.id
    and from_record_master_id = al.master_id
    and to_record_type = 'NfsStore::Manage::Container'
    and to_record_master_id = al.master_id
where 
  ipa_id = :ipa_id
  and extra_log_type = :session_type
  ;
associated_reports.search_attrs:
ipa_id:
  number:
    all: true
    multiple: single


session_type: 
  text: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
    disabled: false
